-- Indian cos invested $1.25 bln overseas in August, up from $1.12 bln in July - RBI
-- By Suvashree Dey Choudhury
-- Thu Sep 11, 2014 06:22AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Sept 11 (Reuters) - Indian corporates invested $1.25 billion overseas in August, higher than $1.12 billion in July but sharply lower than $2.47 billion a year ago, according to data released by the Reserve Bank of India on Thursday.

